ivardefs.name: contentType
ivardefs.desc: Identifies the type of the data in the attachment and allows a method to be chosen to interpret or render the data. Includes mime type parameters such as charset where appropriate.

ivardefs.name: creation
ivardefs.desc: The date that the attachment was first created.

ivardefs.name: data
ivardefs.desc: The actual data of the attachment - a sequence of bytes, base64 encoded.

ivardefs.name: duration
ivardefs.desc: The duration of the recording in seconds - for audio and video.

ivardefs.name: frames
ivardefs.desc: The number of frames in a photo. This is used with a multi-page fax, or an imaging acquisition context that takes multiple slices in a single image, or an animated gif. If there is more than one frame, this SHALL have a value in order to alert interface s

ivardefs.name: hash
ivardefs.desc: The calculated hash of the data using SHA-1. Represented using base64.

ivardefs.name: height
ivardefs.desc: Height of the image in pixels (photo/video).

ivardefs.name: language
ivardefs.desc: The human language of the content. The value can be any valid value according to BCP 47.

ivardefs.name: pages
ivardefs.desc: The number of pages when printed.

ivardefs.name: size
ivardefs.desc: The number of bytes of data that make up this attachment (before base64 encoding, if that is done).

ivardefs.name: title
ivardefs.desc: A label or set of text to display in place of the data.

ivardefs.name: url
ivardefs.desc: A location where the data can be accessed.

ivardefs.name: width
ivardefs.desc: Width of the image in pixels (photo/video).

properties.desc: Base StructureDefinition for Attachment Type: For referring to data content defined in other formats.
